  "prompt": "How can I keep drinking coffee and prevent my teeth from getting stained?",
  "response": "Here are several strategies to minimize coffee stains on teeth:\n\n1. Drink water afterward\n- Rinse your mouth with water after coffee\n- Helps wash away coffee particles\n- Prevents staining\n\n2. Use a straw\n- Minimizes direct contact with teeth\n- Reduces potential staining\n\n3. Practice good oral hygiene\n- Brush teeth within 30 minutes after drinking coffee\n- Use whitening toothpaste\n- Floss regularly\n- Consider electric toothbrush for better cleaning\n\n4. Professional dental cleaning\n- Regular cleanings help remove surface stains\n- Dental hygienist can provide deeper cleaning\n\n5. Dental whitening options\n- Professional teeth whitening treatments\n- At-home whitening strips\n- Whitening gel or trays\n\n6. Modify coffee consumption\n- Drink coffee in shorter periods\n- Avoid sipping coffee over extended time\n- Reduces exposure time to teeth\n\n7. Consider coffee alternatives\n- Less staining teas\n- Lighter roast coffees (lighter roasts stain less)\n\n8. Add milk\n- Milk proteins can help reduce staining potential\n- Lighter colored coffee tends to stain less\n\nRemember, moderation and good oral hygiene are key to preventing coffee stains.",
